1. J2ME  -- java two Micro edition
  Tools 
    1. java (JDK 1.8)
    2. wireless Tool kit 2.5
  Development 
    1.java class extends MIDLet -- it contains life cycle methods
    2.Display -- > Forms ---> Components 
    3.event handling 
        1.CommandListener     -->   public void commandAction(Command command, Displayable displayable)
        2.ItemStateListener   -->   public void itemStateChanged(Item item) 

2. Android -- open source (OS)
    Tools
    1. java (JDK above 1.8)
    2. Android Studio ver 4
    
    Development
    1. SDK -- > software development kit
    2. Gradle -->  ver 3.5 Build Tool
    3. .apk --> android package kit
    4. manifest -->  Agreement between android application and os(contains all Ativity,layout files, and properties of application)
    5. Ativity  -- > it contatins Business Logic(functionality)
       layout --> Collection of view (Content to be displayed on screen)
    6. res -- > resources values,drawables,mipmap,layouts
    7. drawables -- > contains all images in application
    8. values (folder) --> strings , color, styles
    9. constraint:  ,Linear: orientation , grid : numrow .. ,table : row, relative : layout_above ..  
    10 AVD  -- > Android Virtual Device 

3. Flutter 
    1.Hybrid Cross platform framework 
    2.There is no seperation of view and control 
    3.language  --  .dart
    4.widgets 
